---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
import JsonLd from '../components/JsonLd.astro';

const title = "Automated Client Reporting for Accounting Firms: Stop Rebuilding the Same Report";
const description = "How accounting and CPA firms eliminate monthly reporting busywork — QBO period-close triggers, branded PDFs, and live dashboards delivered before clients ask for them.";
const url = "https://www.5cypress.com/automate-client-reporting";

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": title,
  "description": description,
  "url": url,
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "5 Cypress Automation",
    "url": "https://www.5cypress.com"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "5 Cypress Automation",
    "url": "https://www.5cypress.com"
  },
  "datePublished": "2025-01-01",
  "dateModified": "2025-04-01"
};

const steps = [
  { n: "1", label: "QBO period closes", desc: "The system detects the accounting period close in QuickBooks Online." },
  { n: "2", label: "Data pulled per client", desc: "Balance sheet, P&L, and any custom metrics are pulled via QBO API for each client automatically." },
  { n: "3", label: "Report generated", desc: "A branded PDF and a live web dashboard are generated — no templates to fill in, no exports to format." },
  { n: "4", label: "Optional: AI narrative", desc: "An AI-written plain-English summary of the period highlights is added to the report (optional, partner-reviewed)." },
  { n: "5", label: "Partner review (optional)", desc: "Before delivery, a one-click approval step lets the partner review and approve — or override — any report." },
  { n: "6", label: "Delivered by email", desc: "The report is sent to the client by email. Delivery is logged with timestamp. No one builds anything manually." }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <JsonLd data={jsonLd} />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-inner reveal">
        <span class="lead-in">Client Reporting</span>
        <h1>Stop rebuilding the<br /><em>same report every month</em></h1>
        <p class="hero-deck">
          Monthly client reports are accounting firms&apos; most consistent time sink.
          Here is how automation eliminates the work without changing what clients receive.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The problem -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose-container">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <h2>The reporting treadmill</h2>
        <p>
          Ask a staff accountant at almost any small firm what they do between the 1st
          and the 5th of every month, and the answer is some version of the same thing:
          pull the QBO export, paste it into the branded template, adjust the formatting,
          generate the PDF, send the email. For each client. Every month.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is not skilled work. It is repetition. And yet it consumes a meaningful
          portion of staff time every single month — time that cannot be billed, cannot
          be delegated to a junior without close review, and does not get easier with experience.
        </p>
        <p>
          The information needed to produce these reports already exists in QuickBooks Online.
          The only reason a human is involved is that no one has connected the trigger (period close)
          to the output (branded report + delivery) without a person in the middle.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How automation works -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose-container">
      <h2 class="section-heading reveal">What automated client reporting looks like</h2>
      <div class="steps-flow">
        {steps.map((s) => (
          <div class="step reveal">
            <div class="step-num">{s.n}</div>
            <div class="step-body">
              <div class="step-label">{s.label}</div>
              <p class="step-desc">{s.desc}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What you keep -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose-container">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <h2>What the partner keeps control of</h2>
        <p>
          Automated reporting does not mean unsupervised reporting. The system is built
          with a configurable review step: before any report goes out, the partner receives
          a notification and a one-click approval link. If everything looks right, approve
          and the email sends. If something needs adjustment, edit the draft before it delivers.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most firms turn off the mandatory review step after the first quarter, once they
          have confidence in the output. Some keep it for high-value clients or any month
          where significant advisory context needs to be added.
        </p>
        <h2>What clients receive</h2>
        <p>
          From the client perspective, the experience is the same — or better. They receive
          a professionally formatted PDF and a link to a live web dashboard showing their
          financials updated through the prior period. The email arrives reliably before
          the 5th of the month instead of whenever someone got around to it.
        </p>
        <p>
          The optional AI narrative summary is written in plain English — not accounting jargon —
          and highlights the three or four most meaningful numbers from the period. Clients
          who previously ignored reports start reading them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Insight -->
  <section class="section insight-section">
    <div class="container prose-container">
      <div class="insight-box reveal">
        <div class="insight-label">Time math</div>
        <p>
          A firm with 20 monthly reporting clients typically spends 8-15 hours per month
          on manual report production. At a fully-loaded staff cost of $35-50/hr, that is
          $280-$750 per month in labor for work that produces zero revenue. The automation
          pays for itself in the first quarter.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose-container">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <h2>The Monthly Client Snapshot service</h2>
        <p>
          We build automated client reporting systems for accounting and CPA firms. Setup
          takes 10-14 business days. It connects to your existing QBO and delivers branded
          reports to your existing clients — no new tools for them to learn, no migration
          required from your side.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row reveal">
        <Button href="/services/monthly-client-snapshot" variant="primary">See Monthly Client Snapshots</Button>
        <Button href="/#book" variant="secondary">Book a scoping call</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-section {
    padding: var(--space-32) 0 var(--space-20);
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 50% at 50% 0%, rgba(93,140,93,0.12) 0%, transparent 70%);
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .hero-inner h1 {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .hero-deck {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 60ch;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .prose-container {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-4);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .steps-flow {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border-brand);
    padding-left: var(--space-8);
    margin-left: var(--space-4);
  }

  .step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-5) 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .step::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: calc(-1 * var(--space-8) - 5px);
    top: calc(var(--space-5) + 0.35rem);
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    background: var(--brand-primary);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .step-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--brand-primary);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .step-label {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }

  .step-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .insight-section {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .insight-box {
    background: rgba(93,140,93,0.06);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-brand);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-10);
  }

  .insight-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--brand-primary-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .insight-box p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }
</style>
